  "prompt": "Do Jains belong to the OBC category?",
  "response": "Jainism is primarily considered a religious community rather than a caste-based one. In India, Jains are generally categorized under the \"General\" category and are not typically classified as Other Backward Classes (OBC). However, there might be exceptions at the state level, where specific sub-sects or economically weaker sections within the Jain community could be considered for reservation under OBC or other categories, based on local government policies.\n\nIt's essential to consult the specific reservation and classification policies of individual states or refer to official government notifications to get the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding the classification of Jains or any other community under the OBC category.",
